1 modification to such curricula specified by the department through rules adopted pursuant to
2 sections 190.001 to 190.245;
3 (3) Paramedic accreditation requirements. Paramedic training programs shall be
4 accredited as required by the National Registry of Emergency Medical Technicians;
5 (4) Initial licensure testing requirements. Initial paramedic licensure testing shall be
6 through the national registry of EMTs;
7 (5) (a) Continuing education and relicensure requirements.
8 (b) a. The department shall require each emergency medical technician and each
9 advanced emergency medical technician, including each paramedic, to receive the following
10 training as part of the continuing education requirements for relicensure:
11 (i) Any licensee who submits an application for relicensure before January 1, 2028, shall
12 have completed one hour of sex and human trafficking training, consistent with the guidelines
13 established in section 27.170, before such submission;
14 (ii) Any licensee who submits an application for relicensure after December 31, 2027,
15 and before January 1, 2029, shall have completed two hours of sex and human trafficking
16 training, consistent with the guidelines established in section 27.170, before such submission;
17 (iii) Any licensee who submits an application for relicensure after December 31, 2028,
18 and before January 1, 2030, shall have completed three hours of sex and human trafficking
19 training, consistent with the guidelines established in section 27.170, before such submission;
20 and
21 (iv) Any licensee who submits an application for relicensure after December 31, 2029,
22 and before January 1, 2031, shall have completed four hours of sex and human trafficking
23 training, consistent with the guidelines established in section 27.170, before such submission.
24
25 The training may be conducted online, shall be consistent with the guidelines established in
26 section 210.1505, and shall be available at no cost to the personnel identified in this section and
27 all ambulance services and fire departments. The training may be counted toward elective topics
28 as determined by the department, provided that the content is approved by the department as
29 established by regulation.
30 b. The provisions of this paragraph shall become effective on January 1, 2027, and shall
31 expire on December 31, 2031; and
32 (6) Ability to speak, read and write the English language.
33 3. Application for all levels of emergency medical technician license shall be made upon
34 such forms as prescribed by the department in rules adopted pursuant to sections 190.001 to
35 190.245. The application form shall contain such information as the department deems
36 necessary to make a determination as to whether the emergency medical technician meets all the
37 requirements of sections 190.001 to 190.245 and rules promulgated pursuant to sections 190.001
38 to 190.245.
